{{The Holocaust}}

This is a '''selected bibliography and other resources for [[The Holocaust]]'''.

== Bibliography ==
=== Historical studies ===
* [[Yehuda Bauer|Bauer, Yehuda]]. ''Rethinking the Holocaust''. Yale University Press; New Ed edition, 2002. ISBN 0-300-09300-4.
* [[Yehuda Bauer|Bauer, Yehuda]]. ''Jews for Sale? Nazi–Jewish Negotiations 1933–1945''. Yale University Press, 1994. ISBN 0-300-06852-2.
* [[Michael Berenbaum|Berenbaum, Michael]], ''A Mosaic of Victims: Non-Jews Persecuted and Murdered by the Nazis'' (1990)
* [[Karel C. Berkhoff|Berkhoff, Karel C.]] ''Harvest of Despair : Life and Death in Ukraine under Nazi Rule'' (2004)
* [[Horst Biesold|Biesold, Horst]]. ''Crying Hands: Eugenics and Deaf People in Nazi Germany'' (2004)
* [[Edwin Black|Black, Edwin]]. ''[[The Transfer Agreement]]'' (1984)
* [[Edwin Black|Black, Edwin]]. ''[[IBM and the Holocaust]]'' (2001)
* [[Edwin Black|Black, Edwin]]. ''Nazi Nexus: America's Corporate Connections to Hitler's Holocaust''. Washington, DC: Dialog Press, 2009. ISBN 0-914-15309-2.
* [[Edwin Black|Black, Edwin]]. ''The Farhud: The Arab-Nazi Alliance in the Holocaust''. Washington, DC: Dialog Press, 2010. ISBN 0-914-15314-5.
* [[Randolph Braham|Braham, Randolph L.]], ''The Politics of Genocide: The Holocaust in Hungary'' 2 vols. Boulder:Social Science Monographs, distributed by Columbia University Press) (rev. and enlarged, (1994) ISBN  0-8803-3247-6
*[[Martin Broszat|Broszat, Martin]] "Hitler and the Genesis of the ‘Final Solution’: An Assessment of David Irving’s Theses"" pages 73-125 from ''Yad Vashem Studies'', Volume 13,1979; reprinted pages 390-429 in ''Aspects of the Third Reich'' edited by H.W. Koch, London: Macmillan, (1985) ISBN 0-333-35272-6.
* [[Christopher R. Browning|Browning, Christopher R]]. ''The Origins of the Final Solution: The Evolution of Nazi Jewish Policy, September 1939-March 1942'' (2004)
*Burleigh, Michael & Wippermann, Wolfgang ''The Racial State : Germany 1933-1945'', Cambridge : Cambridge University Press, (1991) ISBN 0-521-39114-8.
* [[Lucy Davidowicz|Davidowicz, Lucy]], ''[[The War Against the Jews|The War Against the Jews : 1933-1945]]'' (1975).
* [[Norman Davies|Davies, Norman]] and Lukas, Richard C. ''Forgotten Holocaust: The Poles Under German Occupation 1939-1944'', (2001, c1996)
* Dean, Martin: ''Robbing the Jews - The Cofiscation of Jewish Property in the Holocaust, 1935 - 1945'', Cambridge University Press, 2008.
* [[Deborah Dwork|Dwork, Deborah]]. [[Robert Jan Van Pelt]], ''Auschwitz: 1270 to the Present'' (1996)
* [[Deborah Dwork|Dwork, Deborah]] and [[Jan Van Pelt, Robert]]. ''Holocaust: A History'' (2002)
* Ehrenreich, Eric. "The Nazi Ancestral Proof: Genealogy, Racial Science, and the Final Solution" (2007) ISBN 978-0-253-34945-3.
* [[Suzanne Evans|Evans, Suzanne]]. ''Forgotten Crimes: The Holocaust and People with Disabilities'' (2004)
* [[Saul Friedländer|Friedländer, Saul]]. ''Nazi Germany and the Jews : Volume 1: The Years of Persecution 1933-1939'' (1998); Volume 2: ''Nazi Germany and the Jews 1939-1945: The Years of Extermination''. HarperCollins, 2007.
* [[Henry Friedlander|Friedlander, Henry]]. ''The Origins of Nazi Genocide: From Euthanasia to the Final Solution'' (1997, c1995)
* [[Martin Gilbert|Gilbert, Martin]]. ''Auschwitz and the Allies'' (1983, c198l)
* [[Martin Gilbert|Gilbert, Martin]]. ''The Holocaust: A History of the Jews of Europe during the Second World War'' (New York, 1985) ISBN 0-8050-0348-7
* [[Martin Gilbert|Gilbert, Martin]]. ''The Routledge Atlas of the Holocaust,'' Routledge, New York, 2002. ISBN 0-415-28145-8
* [[Gunter Grau|Grau, Gunter]] & [[Claudia Shoppmann|Shoppmann, Claudia]]. ''The Hidden Holocaust?: Gay and Lesbian Persecution in Germany 1933-45'' (1995)
* [[Israel Gutman|Gutman, Israel]], [[Yisrael Gutman|Gutman, Yisrael]], and [[Michael Berenbaum|Berenbaum, Michael]], eds. ''Anatomy of the Auschwitz death camp'' (1994)  ISBN  0-2533-2684-2
* [[Patricia Heberer|Heberer, Patricia]]. ''Children during the Holocaust'' (2011)
* [[Sonja Hedgepeth|Hedgepeth, Sonja]] & [[Rochelle Saidel|Saidel, Rochelle]].  ''Sexual Violence against Jewish Women during the Holocaust'' (2010)
* [[Raul Hilberg|Hilberg, Raul]]. ''[[The Destruction of the European Jews]]'', vol. 1-3 (2003, c1961)
* [[Raul Hilberg|Hilberg, Raul]]. ''Perpetrators, Victims, Bystanders: The Jewish Catastrophe 1933-1945'', (1992)
* ''The Holocaust Chronicle'', (2001)
* [[Mark Klempner|Klempner, Mark]]. ''The Heart Has Reasons: Holocaust Rescuers and Their Stories of Courage'' (The Pilgrim Press, 2006) ISBN 0-8298-16992
* [[Gunter Lewy|Lewy, Gunter]]. ''The Nazi Persecution of the Gypsies'' (2001)
* {{cite book |last=Longerich |first=Peter |authorlink=Peter Longerich |year=2010 |title=Holocaust: The Nazi Persecution and Murder of the Jews |location=Oxford |publisher=University Press |isbn=978-0-19-280436-5}}
* [[Clarence Lusane|Lusane, Clarence]]. ''Hitler's Black Victims: The Historical Experience of Afro-Germans, European Blacks, Africans and African Americans in the Nazi Era'' (2002)
* [[Richard Plant (writer)|Plant, Richard]]. ''The Pink Triangle: The Nazi War Against Homosexuals'' (1988)
*[[Detlev Peukert|Peukert, Detlev]] “The Genesis of the `Final Solution’ from the Spirit of Science” pages 234-252 from ''Reevaluating the Third Reich'' edited by Thomas Childers and Jane Caplan, New York: Holmes & Meier, 1994 ISBN 0-8419-1178-9.
*[[Michael Mayer|Mayer, Michael]]{{dn|date=July 2011}} ''Staaten als Täter. Ministerialbürokratie und 'Judenpolitik' in NS-Deutschland und Vichy-Frankreich. Ein Vergleich. Preface by Horst Möller and Georges-Henri Soutou'' München, Oldenbourg, 2010 (Studien zur Zeitgeschichte; 80). ISBN 978-3-486-58945-0. (Comparative study of anti-Jewish policy implemented by the Government in Nazi-Germany, by German occupational forces in France and by the semi-autonomic French Government in Vichy)
* [[Radu Ioanid|Ioanid, Radu]]. ''The Holocaust in Romania: The Destruction of Jews and Gypsies Under the Antonescu Regime, 1940-1944'' (2001)
* [[Dalia Ofer|Ofer, Dalia]] & [[Lenore Weitzman|Weitzman, Lenore]]. ''Women in the Holocaust'' (1999)
* Satloff, Robert. " Among the Righteous: Lost Stories from the Holocaust's Long Reach into Arab Lands (Public Affairs, 2006)
* [[Seymour Rossel|Rossel, Seymour]].  ''The Holocaust: The World and the Jews, 1933-1945'' (1992).
* [[Schleunes, Karl A]]. ''The Twisted Road to Auschwitz: Nazi Policy Toward German Jews, 1933-1939'' (1990, c1970)
* {{cite book |last=Snyder |first=Timothy |authorlink=Timothy Snyder |year=2010 |title=[[Bloodlands: Europe Between Hitler and Stalin]] |location=London |publisher=The Bodley Head |isbn=978-0-224-08141-2}}
* [[United States Holocaust Memorial Museum]], ''Historical Atlas of the Holocaust'', Macmillan Publishing (1996)

