* [[Primo Levi|Levi, Primo]]. ''[[If This Is a Man]]'' and ''[[The Truce]]'', published separately in the U.S. as ''Survival At Auschwitz'' and ''The Reawakening'' (1995)
* [[Primo Levi|Levi, Primo]]. ''[[The Drowned and the Saved]]'' (1985)
* [[Filip Müller]]. ''Eyewitness Auschwitz: Three Years in the Gas Chambers at Auschwitz'' (1999, c1979)
* [[Sara Nomberg-Przytyk|Nomberg-Przytyk, Sara]]. ''Auschwitz: True Tales from a Grotesque Land'' (1985)
* [[Miklos Nyiszli|Nyiszli, Miklos]]. ''Auschwitz : A Doctor's Eyewitness Account'' (2001)
* [[Henry Orenstein|Orenstein, Henry]].  "I Shall Live: Surviving against all odds, 1939-1945" (1987), ISBN 0-8253-0441-5
* [[Carol Rittner|Rittner, Carol]] & [[John K. Roth|Roth, John]]. ''Different Voices: Women and the Holocaust'' (1998)
* [[Pierre Seel|Seel, Pierre]]. ''I, Pierre Seel, Deported Homosexual: A Memoir of Nazi Terror'' (1995)
* [[Lyn Smith|Smith, Lyn]], ''[[Forgotten Voices of the Holocaust]]'' (2005), [[Ebury Press]] ISBN 9780091898267
* [[Rudolf Vrba|Vrba, Rudolf]]. First published as ''I Cannot Forgive'' by Sidgwick and Jackson, Grove Press, 1963, ISBN 0-394-62133-6; also published as ''Escape from Auschwitz: I Cannot Forgive''; latest edition ''I Escaped from Auschwitz'', Barricade Books, 2002, ISBN 1-56980-232-7.
* [[Gerda Weissmann Klein|Weissmann Klein, Gerda]]. ''All But My Life'' (1995)
* [[Simon Wiesenthal|Wiesenthal, Simon]] and James, Harry, et al. ''The Sunflower: On the Possibilities and Limits of Forgiveness'' (1998, c1997)
* [[Yitzhak Zuckerman|Zuckerman, Yitzhak]]. ''A Surplus of Memory: Chronicle of the Warsaw Ghetto Uprising'' (1993)
* [[Walter Winter|Winter, Walter]]. ''Winter Time: Memoirs of a German [[Sinti|Sinto]] who Survived Auschwitz'' (2004)
* [[Moyshe Rekhtman]]. [[Here My Home Once Stood (book)]] (2008) ISBN 0-615-21703-6

