===Holocaust education===
*[http://blackisacolor.com/  An artistic portrayal of the Holocaust and its significance (Artist: Stan Lebovic)] The artwork, developed for Black is a Color, is meant to depict the heroic posture humanity has assumed in this post-Holocaust world, and present it to both humanity and G-d. For humanity it should serve as a reminder of the worth of their actions, and for G-d a testament to the worth of G-d's creations.
*[http://www.hedpuk.org/ The Holocaust Education Development Programme (HEDP)]. The Holocaust Education Development Programme (HEDP) is run by the Institute of Education (IOE), University of London and jointly funded by the Pears Foundation and the Department for Children, Schools and Families (DCSF) with support from the Holocaust Educational Trust (HET). Its overarching aim is to help teachers teach about the Holocaust in effective and thought-provoking ways.
*[http://muweb.millersville.edu/~holo-con/ Millersville University Annual Holocaust Conference]
*[http://www.ericdigests.org/1992-3/holocaust.htm "Remember Our Faces"--Teaching about the Holocaust.]
*[http://www.chabad.org/library/article.asp?AID=108398 Belief in God After the Holocaust]
*[http://www.rutexcertp.php Rut Matthijsen Excerpt: A Holocaust Rescuer Discusses How the Holocaust Might Best Be Taught]

